  Title: Tezos SDK For Unity - Examples
  Icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 73b690bc18148b74cadae11bf30aafe7, type: 3}
  Sections:
  - TextHeading: Welcome
    TextSubheading: Tezos SDK For Unity
    TextBody: The Tezos SDK for Unity invites developers to discover the future of
      Web3 gaming. This complete kit empowers game developers to connect to and utilize
      the Tezos blockchain.
    LinkName: OpenTezos.com/gaming/unity-sdk/
    LinkUrl: https://opentezos.com/gaming/unity-sdk/
    PingObjectName: 
    PingObjectGuid: 
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
  - TextHeading: Getting Started
    TextSubheading: Examples
    TextBody: User connects to the blockchain with a Tezos-compatible mobile wallet.
    LinkName: 
    LinkUrl: 
    PingObjectName: Example01_Authentication
    PingObjectGuid: 791e64f89d8236f4ab4fb4fddf9b4204
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
  - TextHeading:
    TextSubheading:
    TextBody: User checks ownership of a given NFT. In production, this may unlock
      related game features.
    LinkName:
    LinkUrl:
    PingObjectName: Example02_NFTTokenGating
    PingObjectGuid: af38c5d306baabc46865c0fecd53c044
    MenuItemName:
    MenuItemPath:
  - TextHeading: Architecture
    TextSubheading: Full Stack Overview
    TextBody: 'A Tezos-integrated Unity game spans five layers: (1) Unity Game - your
      C# scripts call ITezosAPI via TezosSingleton.Instance. (2) Tezos Unity SDK -
      manages wallet sessions and surfaces C# events via ITezosAPI.MessageReceiver.
      (3) Beacon Wallet - the player''s mobile wallet app signs operations; private
      keys never leave the device. (4) Tezos RPC / TzKT Indexer - RPC nodes broadcast
      signed transactions; TzKT provides a fast REST API for querying token ownership.
      (5) Smart Contracts - FA2 contracts store NFT ownership records on-chain.'
    LinkName: TzKT API Reference
    LinkUrl: https://api.tzkt.io
    PingObjectName:
    PingObjectGuid:
    MenuItemName:
    MenuItemPath:
  - TextHeading: Wallet Authentication
    TextSubheading: How It Works
    TextBody: 'Authentication uses the Beacon open standard - no password or API key
      is involved. Flow: (1) Call tezos.ConnectWallet(). (2) The SDK generates a Beacon
      pairing request. (3) On desktop a QR code is shown; on mobile a deep link opens
      the wallet app. (4) The player approves the connection in their wallet. (5) The
      SDK fires MessageReceiver.AccountConnected with the player''s tz1... address.
      (6) Your game receives the address and updates its state. The address is a public
      identifier - no private key ever touches your game code.'
    LinkName: Beacon Protocol Docs
    LinkUrl: https://docs.walletbeacon.io
    PingObjectName: Example01_Authentication
    PingObjectGuid: 791e64f89d8236f4ab4fb4fddf9b4204
    MenuItemName:
    MenuItemPath:
  - TextHeading: NFT Verification
    TextSubheading: How It Works
    TextBody: 'NFT ownership lives in FA2 smart contracts on-chain, not in the SDK
      or your game. Flow: (1) Player connects their wallet. (2) Call tezos.IsOwnerOfToken(address,
      contract, tokenId). (3) TezosExtensions.cs sends a GET request to the TzKT API.
      (4) TzKT returns matching balance records from the FA2 contract ledger. (5) A
      non-empty result means the player holds the token - unlock the feature. TzKT
      is used instead of direct RPC because it pre-indexes FA2 ledgers as a simple
      REST API, avoiding the need to parse raw Michelson contract storage.'
    LinkName:
    LinkUrl:
    PingObjectName: Example02_NFTTokenGating
    PingObjectGuid: af38c5d306baabc46865c0fecd53c044
    MenuItemName:
    MenuItemPath:
  HasLoadedLayout: 0
